The paper deals with graph theory and specifically the queue-number of graphs, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and data structures (cs.DS). The fact that the paper focuses on planar graphs suggests that it may also fall under computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of layered partitions and treewidth also suggests connections to graph theory (cs.GT) and algorithms (cs.LG).
